.nh
.TH "PGMCTL" "1" "May 2026" "pgman-proxy" "pgmctl Manual"

.SH NAME
pgmctl-restart - Restart a peer's PostgreSQL or the pgman-proxy process itself


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBpgmctl restart --target= [--target-node ] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Two modes:

.PP
--target=postgres
    Restarts the LOCAL Postgres on the peer the request lands on. Use
    --endpoint to direct the request to a specific peer (or rely on
    the active context). Engine emits state-transition events; if the
    target is the current primary, a failover may follow.

.PP
--target=proxy
    Restarts the pgman-proxy process itself on the target peer. The
    peer MUST be running under a process supervisor (tini / systemd /
    k8s / process-compose) that will bring it back; otherwise the
    server returns 412 supervisor_not_detected.

.PP
Cluster-affecting in both modes; requires typed cluster name (or
--force --cluster ).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for restart

.PP
\fB--target\fP="postgres"
	What to restart: postgres | proxy

.PP
\fB--target-node\fP=""
	Node id (required for --target=proxy)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--cluster\fP=""
	Expected cluster id; pinned before any cluster-affecting op

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	Path to pgmctl config (overrides $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/pgmctl/config.yaml)

.PP
\fB--context\fP=""
	Configured context name

.PP
\fB--endpoint\fP=""
	Single-shot pgman-proxy endpoint override

.PP
\fB--force\fP[=false]
	Skip cluster-name confirmation (requires --cluster )

.PP
\fB--insecure-skip-tls-verify\fP[=false]
	Disable TLS verification (warned)

.PP
\fB--insecure-skip-version-check\fP[=false]
	Proceed despite minor / major version skew

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Suppress ANSI escapes unconditionally

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format (table, json, yaml, wide)

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--strict\fP[=false]
	Treat WARN as non-zero exit

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=10s
	Overall command timeout

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=0]
	Increase verbosity (-v / -vv / -vvv)

.PP
\fB-y\fP, \fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Skip single-resource confirmation prompts


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBpgmctl(1)\fP
